## Entry format

Use the `req()` helper in the generator script:

```python
req("Endpoint Name", "METHOD", f"{BASE}/api/path", ["api","path"],
    query=[q("param","value")],           # optional query params
    body=body_json({"key": "value"}),      # optional request body
    auth=noauth(),                         # only for public endpoints
    events=id_extract_test("varName"))     # only for create endpoints
```

## Auto-generated test scripts

Every endpoint gets test scripts automatically via the `auto_test(method, name)` function when no custom `events` are passed to `req()`. The auto-tests include:

| HTTP Method | Auto-generated tests |
|---|---|
| GET | Status 200, Content-Type JSON, Response body not empty, No server error (500/502/503) |
| POST (create) | Status 200 or 201, Content-Type JSON, Body not empty, No server error |
| POST (auth/login) | Status 200, Content-Type JSON, Body not empty, No server error |
| POST (other) | Status 200, Content-Type JSON, Body not empty, No server error |
| PUT / PATCH | Status 200, Content-Type JSON, No server error |
| DELETE | Status 200 or 204, Content-Type JSON (if body present) |

Custom test events override auto-tests. Use these helpers for special endpoints:

| Helper | When to use |
|---|---|
| `jwt_extract_test()` | Auth endpoints that return a JWT (signin, signup, refresh, verify-login-otp) |
| `id_extract_test("varName")` | Create endpoints that return a resource ID to chain into subsequent requests |
| `status_test(code)` | Simple single status code assertion |

## Rules

- Public endpoints (no JWT required) must have `auth=noauth()`
- Create endpoints should use `events=id_extract_test("variableName")` to auto-store the created ID
- Auth endpoints (signin/signup) should use `events=jwt_extract_test()` to auto-store JWT
- Endpoints without custom `events` automatically get method-appropriate test scripts
- Always regenerate the JSON after updating the script -- never edit `postman-collection.json` directly
